ltsp (0.43-0+vagrant.3) experimental; urgency=low

  * mount /proc in the chroot before installing additional packages
  * ltsp-update-kernels, ltsp-update-sshkeys:
    - grab LTSPROOT info from environment variables, when possible.
  * ltsp-build-client:
    - pass ltsp-update-kernels and ltsp-update-sshkeys variables
    - really install udhcpc, devfsd and udev by default
    - do "apt-get dist-upgrade" after updating the package lists
    - create empty /etc/hostname and /etc/hosts files
  * more bindfiles in ltsp-client-setup: syslog.conf, fstab, nbd-client

